values:
Andrew got off work today at 4:30 as usual.  And being Wednesday, I went with him to pick up his paycheck and then cash it - as usual.  So right after that we go to McDonald's with my family (well, mom, ericka, kara, cousin amanda).  I'm thinkin', okay... this could be a good thing right?  Wrong.  We get there, not 2 minutes after everyone is sitting down, kara starts it again.  She blows a straw wrapper at Andrew, and then dares him to throw a fry at her.  Well duh, he will.  She knew this.  So he does and they end up being themselves and doing their thing.  Well eventually Andrew is just like Kara, shut up and knock it off, this is getting old.  She doesn't - she just stares at him and is super snotty and so he gets up and walks away.  I am thoroughly pissed off by then.  Kara yells at me saying I only yell at her and tell her to stop when even mom said "Carisa told him to stop too!".  Well then kara just brings up all this crap from the past and yeah.  UGH I was pissed.  But anyways, I ended up driving home...  Andrew has to leave right away so he gets into his car and I ask him if I can have a hug or something, and he's like but I have to go.  And then I'm like fine, whatever... so then Miss Thing comes up to the car (Kara by the way) and tells him something which I can't hear and he rolls up the window so I can't hear them talking.... and he's sitting there and they're talking for like a minute... and yet I can't even get a hug.... UGH... I am in SUCH a bad mood right now.

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/13642.html

I've been working on a "wizard robe" looking thing for Andrew... he bought all the fabric and everything, but I get to make it. lol, he spent over $55 on the stuff. lol. But I like doing stuff for him.  Makes me feel good.  Plus he likes it too. lol.

We went to dinner with his parents tonight. It went okay.  She's one of those types of people who ... if the do something for you like make dinner and spend time on something, they almost need you to want to eat it and love it or they feel bad type of thing.  So I always try her desserts and dinners and stuff when she invites me over. lol.  Andrew doesn't always have the dessert, but I do.  I want her to like me!  Her food is awesome too! lol  After dinner, Andrew's little brother, Noah, and I jumped on the trampoline while Andrew talked to his parents.  It was pretty fun.  he's 6 years old. lol, he's a pretty cool little kid though - who is obviously Andrew's little brother. lol. it's written all over him.  :)

But I'm finally starting to get sleepy, and it's 2 in the morning.  Everyone else went to bed at 12. lol.  I haven't been able to sleep for about a month though.  It sucks. Cuz I hate sleeping in past 11.  Hate it.  But church is tomorrow morning, so I'll be up around 8 or 8:30. lol.  I'll be tired.  Oh well.

night everyone!

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/13414.html

I had my meeting with Mrs. Beilen this morning.  I won't be able to go PSEO until second semester, in the spring.  Which isn't too bad, I'm fine with that.  It's probably better anyway, because by then I will for sure have my license and mom and dad won't have to drive me there and back every day.  So it's a good thing.

As for the college thing... thanks to my GPA (3.590 as of now)and my ACT score (24), I will get this presidental scholarship or whatever ($1,750 to $5,000) and since dad is a pastor I will also get 10% off my tuition.  It isn't much, especially for how much it costs per year there, but it helps a lot. It's pretty cool.  I haven't applied for any other scholarships yet either... those two things are automatic.  So there's a chance for more..

Andrew and I will probably go out tonight.  We didn't go on our anniversary for certain reasons so we were planning on maybe going tonight.  Since it's payday!  lol.  I'm not sure what we'll do though.

Well I'm going to check up on my MySpace.com thingy.  TTYL.

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/13074.html

So yeah, it's been forever and a weekend since I updated this thing.  But I'm going to try to get back to doing this.  If anyone reads this...?  But anyways.

So I am scared now.  I have been planning on going post secondary this year... but now I don't know if this will work.  Because I didn't realize I had to take the placement test.  Well I knew, but no one told me when I had to take it.  And I guess it was supposed to be by June... two months ago.  Yeah... my mom is friends with a lady who works at RCTC doing that stuff that I'm wondering about, so mom is going to talk to her tomorrow and see what she can do about it. And then tomorrow morning I have a meeting with my guidance counselor about the whole thing and about my schedules and everything.  Hopefully everything works out.  I am praying so hard that it does.

This morning I was so sick... it sucked.  And Andrew called me and he was all worried and stuff.  It was so cute. :)  I felt better later so I changed and everything before he came over after work.  It's weird, I feel totally grungy and like crap when I'm wearing a tee-shirt and no socks or make-up even. lol. So I changed completely, brushed my hair... again..., brushed my teeth again, put on make up and put on socks. lol, then I felt much better. 

Yesterday was Andrew and my 10th anniversary. :) That's a long time!  But it's been awesome.  I love him.  So much.  

But I'm going to go.  I'll try to update this soon.  Instead of 5 months later.  lol.  Laters

Time to drink my cappucino!  :)

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/12985.html

I am SO happy that 3rd quarter is finally over!  But next quarter is going to suck more.  oh well - it's the last quarter and then it's SUMMER!  I hope I can have as many parties as I did last summer, it was so awesome, I just hope it's awesome this year too.

This weekend has the potential of being pretty boring.  The Arivett's are here for the weekend, but the kids are all boys who are all younger and Andrew is gone Friday, Saturday, and part of Sunday.. :(  So we'll see how this goes.

As short as this is... I think I'm done for the night. lol.  Night all!

-Carisa

http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/12411.html

Wow.  This like whole month I have not stopped cleaning!  It has always been something I do when I'm stressed or upset or just pissed, but now it's like all I ever do and I still can't keep up with it!  I clean before I do my homework or anything anymore - it's insane.  My siblings never do their "chore" so I always have to do it for them or it won't get done... it's so annoying, and then I come back later and it's messy again.  GRR!  Mom is even paying me to do kara's chore (laundry).  She's paying me a dollar a load... so far I'm up to $15.  lol.

Mom and Dad let me stay home from school on Friday.  I was so happy.  I'm like never sick so I'm always at school.  When I'm overwhelmed or super stressed, mom lets me stay home sometimes.  Not all the time, but every great once in a while.  I needed that too, I was in a good mood for the whole day... well, until we were coming home from Brick and Amp around 11:30.  Then I cried.  But anyways, enough of that story.

Andrew and I have been great lately too, he's the one I can actually count on.  All the time.  

Mom and Dad left Friday morning (around 7:30 after taking my siblings to school) for Madison, Wisconson.  They went to this Canoecopia thing...? lol  I don't know.  But they get back tomorrow after church sometime.  It is pretty cool, because I can pretty much do whatever without plans, I am "in charge", and Kara is at Lori's all weekend.  Don't get me wrong... I love Kara.  But I can't do anything right by her - no matter how hard I try - so when she isn't around, I can't be wrong... so then I'm not the horrible big sister.  

*sigh*  well I have to finish cleaning... maybe I'll sleep tonight.  Who knows.  Night

-Carisa

Right now I'm just on here until Andrew comes to pick me up for school.  My favorite place to be!  jk.  way jk.  I get to present my bipolar disorder project today.  joy!  lol.  i came home with no homework last night... didn't bring my bag with  me either and then I get home and I realize... I have a worksheet to do... so i get to do that before school... if Andrew comes.  lol.  He always comes later though.  It's alright.  Lately I don't mind.  Nothing to do before school anyway except pretend like I'm doing something in my locker.  So ya know.  yesterday was a pretty productive day for me.  At least at home.  I did three people's chore's... in an hour and a half - plus some.  lol, so yeah.. i was bored.  Well I'm going to go... I don't have anything to say.  See ya!

-Carisa

have a shpadoinkle day!
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/11980.html

So these past couple weeks have NOT been enjoyable.  In some ways they have been, but overall they haven't.  Okay... I take that back.  In just about one way.  I won't get into that though, I don't need to.  

I got my room painted and so I had to take EVERYTHING out of my room... which was really annoying to have to sleep in a room with nothing in it but a bed.  lol.  I got it painted while I was at school Thursday and it's awesome, I love it!  But it was a day or two before I moved stuff in, and I'm still not fully unpacked yet and it's grr-worthy.  Daddy has to put my TV in and stuff so I have to wait for that before most things will get done.

Most things, I will say... are really good in my life.  It's just that the bad things seem to balance with the more and better good things.  If that makes sense.  I'm so happy for the people who are here with me right now... even if some of them won't be later, I'm glad I have them right now.  I need all my friends all the time lately.  

One of the hardest things to deal with right now is the fact that Andrew is going to enlist for the Navy.  Even though he isn't 100% sure, it's very hard.  I want him to follow his dreams though, I love him too much to keep him from doing that.  God has been giving me peace though.  Thank you!

Guys, keep thinking of me and praying for me.  I need you guys all the time... to talk or just to hang out with and do nothing.  I greatly appreciate you all so much.  Don't give up on me over little things... okay?

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/11560.html

Hey.  I love early outs.  I came home and slept.  That was a good thing.  I slept in a weird position too - completely curled up on my side with one arm covering my head.  Strange... yet comfortable and secluded.  I wanted to sleep the week away but that didn't work.  

Yeah, my day basically sucked though, other than the early out part.  Like really sucked.  I feel totally and completely betrayed.  I don't know what I did or why people are doing this to me.  I am utterly confused about this.  I don't know what to do and I'm scared.  I almost lost something very close to me, and I feel that I have lost another.  I feel completely helpless.  I hate these feelings.  Andrew and Erik stopped over earlier, right after I had waken up - I was still in bed though.  (Don't worry, I slept in my clothes, fully dressed, lol)  We talked about some stuff which was pretty cool... and I needed it.  Then I went over to Andrew's a while later and we talked and stuff.  It was one of those up and down moments - but it was needed and overall "good" too.  I can tell that there are going to be some hard struggles to work through with certain circumstances around us.  It's going to be really difficult... but we'll make it.  I thank God that I'm still alive and that I have that someone to help me through it.  Many people don't realize how supportive and everything he is.  

I am kind of emotionally drained right now, so I'm going to go... I am really going to need this Brick and Amp tonight.  I'll have to talk to some people - don't worry certain people, I won't let anything "leak" okay?  Later  God please help me!

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/11459.html

Valentine's Day is pretty cool, lol.  It was my first Valentine's that I actually HAD a Valentine. lol.  So that was awesome.  Sorry to those of you who I may be sounding too uppity.  :(  I don't mean too.  But yeah, I had a good yesterday.  And I also had an awesome today - it's my 4 month anniversary.  Pretty sweet! heehee aaahhh lol, nvm.  Ignore that if you'd like.

You know what I need to do right now?  I need to go work out or something.  ;) no I'm kidding, but I do... like crunches and push-ups kind of thing.  I did last night and Sunday night.  I should tonight too.  I guess it's not good for you to work out right before you go to bed, but that's like the only time I ever feel like it.  lol, oh well.  Bummer for me.  Especially since I've had chocolate and stuff in the past couple days, lol.  Can't be good.

Yesterday was so cool, starting the day with a school delay is always good.  My tests went very, very well.  Homework wasn't too heavy, and it was just a good day!  It was cool, I had nothing to complain about.  lol, maybe school isn't so bad, I mean I do get to talk to my friends and everything, when I usually don't get to any other time.  Except for instant messaging, I rarely talk to most people outside of school.  Like Tani, Marianne, Zach, or Andy... or just about anyone.  Plus, I talk to most people in my grade, not all, but a lot, at least a little bit, and school's the only time I get to.  So it's not a bad thing I guess.  You know... after high school is starting to scare me.  There are some things i want to do, but I don't know if I'm ready.  I mean college for one thing, marriage... I mean wow.  I'm only 16 right now and I'm trying to plan my whole life.  What if I mess up?  What if I make the wrong decisions?  What would that do to me?  I mean... would that ruin my whole life or would it just change it a little bit but still be good?  And that kind of depends on what decision it is...  ugh... I'm scared.  And who will I still talk to after high school?  I'll probably lose the friends I have...  And... even though I still feel like my friendships are conditional instead of unconditional, I don't want to lose what I finally have.  I NEED to stop thinking.  Oh, I know what I need!  I need a party.  I want to invite like EVERYONE!  I would this weekend but I don't know if it's too late of notice.  Maybe not.  Who knows.  I don't know what we'd do, but I just want to have people here, around me, and just hang out, not necessarily doing anything in particular... just... "chill".  I'll think about it.  I just don't want fights to erupt like they usually do - I'm cursed with that.  grr.

I'm going to go though - e-mail needs to be checked.  See ya!

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/11156.html

It's been interesting.  I went over to Andrew's yesterday for a little bit after school, until he had to pick up Noah.  Then he called me later and we talked a little bit.  He and I were both upset about what my dad had said the other night (which I won't get into) so we were kind of half talking about that.  He stopped over later, when he got home from eating out with his family and stuff and we had just pulled in the driveway.  So we talked outside for a little bit and he apologized for a couple things and everything, and I must say - he was being very understanding and mature about the whole thing, just everything.  The situation itself I won't explain. but yeah, then he came inside to use the phone and ended up talking to mom.  After he left, mom, dad, and I talked for a little while.  That wasn't too bad.  So overall, even though it was a tough night, it was a good thing too.  

Andy came over a little bit later and we talked about a lot, for a long time.  That was pretty cool.  Before he left, we were talking about some things that I can totally understand and relate too, more than I think he thinks I can.  That was a confusing sentence, lol.

But yesterday, while I was over at Andrew's, I about started crying so hard.  It wasn't cool.  Someone very close to me isn't doing too well, health wise I guess, and I'm scared to death.  I was bawling Thursday night, and then Andrew called while I was still crying so I talked to him about it and he can relate 100%, so that helped.  And I talked to him about it again yesterday too.  He's just awesome to talk to - especially when I know he'll always be there for me.  I love you Andrew.

But I better go, I might even do some homework... before 10:00 Sunday night. lol.  See ya.  Pray for me please!

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/10914.html

So I went to school... lol. okay duh.  Math went good for the most part, Psych was super slow and boring but it was okay, and World Cultures was boring.  

I left after 3rd hour with Kami and went into Rochester to take my permit test (finally!).  I PASSED!  Oh man, I was ecstatic!  It isn't in my possession yet though, because I went with Kami so mom or dad weren't able to sign it.  They kept all my paper work though and then we can come in soon and mom or dad can sign it, and THEN I get it.  :) I am so happy. After I took it (I got 5 wrong lol but they were stupid reasons, I just didn't read it right or I didn't read all the answers or something), I went up to the desk thing and Kami was in the lobby area and I looked at her and I'm like "Kami!" and gave her a thumbs up and she's like "You passed!  YAY!" But I had to go fill stuff out.  

Then we left and we ran to the Christian book store - Kami had to get a thing or two.  And then we went to Target and picked up my mom's prescription receit... then to Walmart to return my pants that I hated. lol.  And oh, I got a Caribou Coffee!  :)  To celebrate. lol. 

I wanted to go over to Andrew's, but he had to go somewhere so he wasn't home when I got home.  Hopefully I get to see him tonight.

Brandy talked to me online today.  That was kind of weird.  Not bad, but weird.  I haven't talked to Brett since like May and her since April or something, IF I even talked to her.  That was weird.  But yeah.  I guess Brett's changed a lot.  I guess whatever works for him.  lol.  But I have my guy now, so I'm not like "oh man" or anything, LOL.  Don't worry Andrew.  Brett and I are barely friends anymore... we never talk... weirdness.

Andrew - I love you and hope to see you tonight!  *muah* xoxox

-Carisa
    (cherry!)
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/10552.html

Last night I went to a movie with Andrew, finally, we went with Alex and Adam.  It was fun.  Yeah... lol, a night full of 'interesting' meetings. Wow.  lol.  The most interesting, for me at least, was seeing Andrew's ex Kelly there.  That was crazy.  Andrew wasn't feeling good and by the time he got home, around 10:30, he had a fever... poor guy.  I went over there to see him today, his whole family is like worried about me getting sick, but I could really care less. I can't even remember the last time I was sick so whatever.  Kami stayed the night last night.  Amanda was going to but... she changed her mind I guess.  Which sucked.  That's why I went to the movie, I came home and Kara told me that Amanda called to say she wasn't going to come over anymore so I just went to the movie.  *sigh* Doesn't surprise me though...

Today was church, obviously, and that was okay.  I had nursery but there weren't any kids ... but I stayed down there anyway cuz I would have fallen asleep during the sermon. lol.  Aaron stayed down tehre with me too.  

Mom is thinking I should take med's now... for depression.  We'll see how that goes.  Great.

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/10278.html

I DELETED ANYTHING I WROTE HERE.  CUZ YEAH.  SORRY PEOPLES, I'LL JUST QUIT TALKING ANYMORE.  MAYBE THEN I'LL BE A BETTER PERSON.

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/10213.html

Yeah so today was pretty a-okay.  *wink to Zach lol*  yeah anyways.  

School was okay.  I'm tutoring Chris Yannis in Spanish, but he always bails on me so technically I haven't tutored him yet.  If he doesn't stick with a time sometime soon, I'm going to be pissed, cuz I won't get extra credit.  So who knows.  I can't wait until this quarter is over!!!

Ugh I want to scream... LOUDLY!  My flippin' phone is retarded - it hangs up on people, and also gets so staticy and stuff that you can't hear the people but you can hear yourself and others on your side of the phone so loudly that it hurts your ears... I have laundry to do but Kara never got the stuff out of the dryer so that stuff isn't done yet and it's already 10:00, so I'll be up waiting for that.  I haven't been able to sleep all week, it's really pissing me off cuz I've been dead tired for so long.  And I just want to SCREAM!!!  I NEED my girls day out tomorrow - thank you Amanda.  Wow, i need it.  

I still don't feel like I belong to anything... or really anywhere.  I know I belong to someone, just not to something.  Since I quit karate and I have no job... I feel like... unproductive and stuff.  I don't like it.  I need to be busy, I feel more needed and more important.  I should ask Ericka and Kara if I can clean the church occassionally.  I feel important when I'm doing something like that.  I don't know.  I'm weird that way.  Plus it's $32 for four hours.  Not too bad.  Plus it's cool, cuz I can act like a total dork, and no one is there to see me!  lol.

Andrew - you're so awesome.  I love you so much, and I'm glad I'm yours forever.  Thank you for loving me for me.  I won't let you go.  I love you!  Unconditionally!

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/9923.html

I am so ecstatic about the whole no school thing.  Like wow.  Nobody called me this morning though... usually Amanda calls me... or Andrew.  But nobody did... :(.  Yeah, I've been like depressed lately.  Maybe not so much depressed as just down.  But I don't know why.  It's really frustrating, because if I don't know what's causing it, I feel totally helpless.  It sucks.  I think school is a major factor, with so many tests and make up and everything.  Oh, and I'm currently not in karate anymore.  It's just stressing me out so much and it's really frustrating me cuz I can't remember it very well.  I always have too much on my mind to concentrate that much - I lose track of what I'm doing.  I think I'll join again next session (in the fall), but that's still a decision I have to make.

I am also unemployed.  Most of you know that, but it's been a while since I've updated and so I'm putting it in here.  It really pissed me off too - mainly just because I had to work New Years Eve and I find out THAT NIGHT that it was the last night I'd be working.  And then they let me off at 7:00.  So I made like what?  Ten bucks?  Woo flippin hoo.  And it isn't just the fact that I was laid off (yes, I was laid off, not fired), but it was the fact that they quit on me, I wanted to be the one to quit.  But I guess "store went out of business" will look better on my next applications to who knows where.  Jeff just really pisses me off though.  Wow.  So I'm glad I'm done working there, but I'm mad cuz I have no source of income now.  He wasn't that nice to me - he was constantly picking at me, and even my dad.  I mean, picking at me is fine once in a while, although he went overboard many times... but why did he pick at my dad?  I mean seriously...  That's just too far.  So my dad's a pastor!  That doesn't mean I don't do certain things just because of my daddy.  I do things/don't do things for ME.  I don't do drugs or smoke or drink because I don't want to.  I have had many chances to do either one of those - it's me that says no, not my dad.  I know some people don't believe that, like I've been brainwashed or something.  Sorry people, I'm different.  Grr.

And now I'm done whining.  Later all.

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/9665.html

Don't ask about that subject... but I wanted something in there... :)

Anyways.  So it's been a good month and 3 weeks.  :)  Yeah, it's Andrew and my two month next Wednesday!  How awesome!?  Wayness.  

Right now I am chillin... just drinking some caffeine free mt. dew and eating a little bit of mom's sugar free, fat free eclair type stuff. lol.  It's yummy.  I would normally, as every other day, be at Andrew's or he would be here, buuuuuttttt... he and Matt (Schimek) went into Rochester to buy my present! :)  As of right now I know what I'm getting him, but I don't know.  I have this idea but I don't know if it will work, or if I can find the store-bought portion of it.  So I don't know.  Ooh!  I just thought of something else.  Don't know if it will work either though. lol.  oh well.  So yeah, I can't wait until Friday.  Should be fuuuunnnn!  :)  

I have karate tonight... I'm kind of scared to go.  We didn't go last week because testing was going on and I wasn't going to test, either was Aaron or Andrew.  And the week before that we had to skip because we left early Wed. morning for Illinois so we had stuff to do.  *sigh*  oh well.  Crap!  I gotta study that stuff.  Gotta go!  Byes!

-Carisa
http://teeniereece.livejournal.com/9372.html

Hey.  Happy Thanksgiving to you all!  I hope everyone had a great one.  I had a double holiday today, lol, Thanksgiving and Christmas with my mom's side of the family.  It was pretty cool.  I really do have a lot to be thankful for.  I wish my grandparents still did the "go around the table and say a few things you're thankful for" thing, but they don't.  I've always liked to do that for some reason.  I have a great family, even though I sometimes just need to get away from them;  awesome friends who are always there for me; the bestest boyfriend - I love you!!;  my needs are met, even though I don't always get the luxuries some people get, I feel blessed;  a pretty good school, better than some I guess, lol, at least I'm getting an education, and I have that right, unlike many people outside the U.S.;  good health;  freedoms; wow, I could go on and on.  But I won't.  :)  

Yeah, we left Wednesday (around 12:30) afternoon to go to Illinois to spend Thanksgiving and early Christmas with the Ledbetter fam.  We stopped at Andrew's house so I could say goodbye and get my letter :) and dad talked to Jamie for a little bit.  We then stopped by the church so Ericka could get her CD's.
